This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning to train a team of robotic bodyguards, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the use of deep reinforcement learning suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study of primitive and composite reward functions also suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) to evaluate the behavior of the robotic bodyguards.
